# Relay Bus

Monorepo for the Relay Bus project, managed with **Turborepo** and **pnpm**.
Designed for fast onboarding, shared code, and consistent development across the team.

---

## ðŸ“ Repo Structure

```
apps/        # Applications
packages/    # Shared code & configs
```

**Apps**

* `apps/web` â†’ Main Next.js app
* `apps/docs` â†’ Documentation site

**Packages**

* `packages/ui` â†’ Shared UI components
* `packages/eslint-config` â†’ ESLint rules
* `packages/typescript-config` â†’ TypeScript config

---

##  Requirements

* Node.js **11.6.2**
* pnpm **10.26.2**

Install pnpm (one time):

```bash
npm install -g pnpm
```

---

##  Start Development

From the repo root:

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm dev
```

Apps will be available at:

| App  | URL                                            |
| ---- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| Web  | [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) |
| Docs | [http://localhost:3001](http://localhost:3001) |

---

##  Run a Single App

```bash
pnpm --filter web dev
pnpm --filter docs dev
```


> Migration commands depend on the database tool (Prisma / Drizzle / etc).

---

##  Team Rules

* Use **pnpm only** (no npm/yarn lockfiles)
* Shared logic lives in `packages/`
* Do not duplicate code between apps
* Use root scripts whenever possible

---

##  Common Commands

```bash
pnpm dev     # Run all apps
pnpm build   # Build all apps
pnpm lint    # Lint everything
```
